%N A202095 Number of (n+2)X5 binary arrays avoiding patterns 001 and 011 in rows and columns.
%C A202095 Part of a family of width-w binary arrays avoiding 001 and 011 (w=3..9: A202093-A202099) with common formula a(n) = C(alpha+E,E)*C(alpha+O,O)*C(beta+E,E)*C(beta+O,O) where E=ceil(w/2), O=floor(w/2), alpha=floor((n+3)/2), beta=floor((n+2)/2). - _Christian Krause_, Jun 27 2026
%H A202095 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A202095/b202095.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%F A202095 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) +8*a(n-2) -18*a(n-3) -27*a(n-4) +72*a(n-5) +48*a(n-6) -168*a(n-7) -42*a(n-8) +252*a(n-9) -252*a(n-11) +42*a(n-12) +168*a(n-13) -48*a(n-14) -72*a(n-15) +27*a(n-16) +18*a(n-17) -8*a(n-18) -2*a(n-19) +a(n-20). - Proved by _Christian Krause_, Jun 27 2026.
